HEADWORD: Keilhauite
<hw>Keil"hau*ite</hw> <pr>(k⟦imac⟧l"hou*⟦imac⟧t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A mineral of a brownish black color, related to
titanite in form. It consists chiefly of silica, titanium dioxide, lime,
and yttria.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

